WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.730 --> 00:00:02.790
- I can look at a landing page right away

00:00:02.790 --> 00:00:04.850
and know that it's not going to convert.

00:00:04.850 --> 00:00:07.600
On the flip side, I can
also look at a landing page

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:10.580
and know if it's going to
convert exceptionally well.

00:00:10.580 --> 00:00:12.370
Hi everyone, I'm Neil Patel.

00:00:12.370 --> 00:00:14.320
And today, I'm going to share with you

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:17.573
the anatomy of a high
converting landing page.

00:00:17.573 --> 00:00:20.823
(gentle melodic music)

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:24.540
Before we get started,
make sure you subscribe

00:00:24.540 --> 00:00:25.373
to this channel.

00:00:25.373 --> 00:00:27.780
And if you're on YouTube,
click the alert notification.

00:00:27.780 --> 00:00:29.570
that way, when I release more videos

00:00:29.570 --> 00:00:32.130
and more tips, you'll get notified.

00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:33.590
So do you want to know the secret

00:00:33.590 --> 00:00:35.950
to really high converting landing page?

00:00:35.950 --> 00:00:38.540
There's a formula, and I'm
about to share it with you.

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:40.020
And as long as you follow the formula

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:43.640
step by step, you should
produce better results.

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:45.710
But the moment you
don't follow the formula

00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:48.120
step by step, you'll notice
that your conversions

00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:51.210
are going to tank and your
landing pages won't do well.

00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:53.210
So let's get started.

00:00:53.210 --> 00:00:55.790
The first thing you need
to do is clearly state

00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:58.650
your value proposition in a header.

00:00:58.650 --> 00:01:00.210
And this is important, a lot of people,

00:01:00.210 --> 00:01:01.810
like yeah, I'll state
the value proposition

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:02.950
somewhere on the page.

00:01:02.950 --> 00:01:03.783
No.

00:01:03.783 --> 00:01:05.130
The attention span of a human

00:01:05.130 --> 00:01:06.660
is less than a goldfish.

00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:08.940
In other words, if you
can't catch their attention

00:01:08.940 --> 00:01:11.440
in the headline, you're screwed.

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:13.330
Eight out of 10 people
will read your headline,

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:14.520
but only two of the 10

00:01:14.520 --> 00:01:17.250
will read the rest of
the copy on the page.

00:01:17.250 --> 00:01:18.960
In other words, your headline

00:01:18.960 --> 00:01:20.260
is either going to make it where people

00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:21.560
will read the rest of your content,

00:01:21.560 --> 00:01:22.780
or you're going to lose them.

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:25.390
So if you can create amazing headline

00:01:25.390 --> 00:01:27.160
with your value proposition,

00:01:27.160 --> 00:01:31.580
you can attract people to
read the rest of your page.

00:01:31.580 --> 00:01:33.530
Now, the best tip that I can give you,

00:01:33.530 --> 00:01:36.730
because everyone's going to have
a different value proposition,

00:01:36.730 --> 00:01:39.400
is make sure your headline
is something bold,

00:01:39.400 --> 00:01:41.880
you're making a statement, it's short,

00:01:41.880 --> 00:01:42.890
and to the point.

00:01:42.890 --> 00:01:45.030
You don't want something that's run-on.

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:46.990
If you can do that, short, to the point,

00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:48.300
you're making a statement,

00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:52.800
something bold, and ideally
seven, eight words max.

00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:55.180
Maybe around six words ideally,

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:56.270
you'll do much better.

00:01:56.270 --> 00:02:00.210
The moment it's too run-on,
you're going to lose people.

00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:02.140
The second step you need
in your landing page

00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:03.120
is a visual focus.

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:05.340
Whether it's a head shot, product shot,

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:07.830
a video, some sort of visual focus

00:02:07.830 --> 00:02:10.300
where people can put
all their attention to.

00:02:10.300 --> 00:02:12.490
See, the moment someone
goes through a headline,

00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:14.500
they read it, you need
to grab their attention

00:02:14.500 --> 00:02:17.180
with a visual, and you need
to get them to keep going.

00:02:17.180 --> 00:02:19.280
If you just have text and only text,

00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:21.040
and no visuals that people can watch,

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:23.600
you'll find that the
conversions aren't as great.

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:25.180
The higher quality you produce,

00:02:25.180 --> 00:02:26.750
the better off you are.

00:02:26.750 --> 00:02:28.080
The third thing you need

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:30.270
is to outline the features and benefits.

00:02:30.270 --> 00:02:31.950
But it's not just about feature,

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:34.110
you need to more so focus on the benefits.

00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:35.180
So the features are there

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:37.020
because if you don't
talk about the features,

00:02:37.020 --> 00:02:38.760
you're not going to get
as many conversions.

00:02:38.760 --> 00:02:40.480
But the benefits are the key.

00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:42.690
People don't buy something
because of features,

00:02:42.690 --> 00:02:44.070
they buy because of the benefit.

00:02:44.070 --> 00:02:46.210
Typically, benefits are the solution

00:02:46.210 --> 00:02:47.210
to their problem.

00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:49.620
Such as saves you time, saves you money.

00:02:49.620 --> 00:02:51.000
If the benefits aren't there,

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:52.750
and they're not clearly stated,

00:02:52.750 --> 00:02:54.000
you're not going to do well.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:55.960
And you don't want to
just state any benefits.

00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:57.700
Like whatever you think is the benefits

00:02:57.700 --> 00:02:59.040
of the product or service.

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:00.600
You want to talk to your ideal customers.

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:02.600
Find out the problems that they're facing.

00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:04.350
Ideally, your product or solution

00:03:04.350 --> 00:03:06.030
should solve those problems.

00:03:06.030 --> 00:03:08.440
And that should be the benefit.

00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:09.930
How you're solving the problems.

00:03:09.930 --> 00:03:12.580
Don't talk about how you
solve X, Y, and Z problem,

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:13.930
it's more so like, if something

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:15.500
takes a lot of time for people,

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:19.320
you can say, on average, this
saves three hours, right?

00:03:19.320 --> 00:03:21.750
You're letting them know the benefit.

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:23.530
The fourth step is presenting

00:03:23.530 --> 00:03:26.100
a single and focused call to action.

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:27.077
A lot of people are like,

00:03:27.077 --> 00:03:28.497
"Oh, I've got a landing page.

00:03:28.497 --> 00:03:30.830
"I'm going to put a call
to action everywhere."

00:03:30.830 --> 00:03:31.670
You could do that.

00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:33.220
And for some products, it works.

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:34.900
But not for most.

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:35.890
The reason you want to have

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:38.020
a single, focused call to action,

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:40.320
and eventually after
that one call to action,

00:03:40.320 --> 00:03:42.010
you can have more later down,

00:03:42.010 --> 00:03:43.770
but when you have your headline,

00:03:43.770 --> 00:03:44.970
your visual focus,

00:03:44.970 --> 00:03:46.220
you're talking about your benefits,

00:03:46.220 --> 00:03:49.160
your solutions, you're
answering the objections.

00:03:49.160 --> 00:03:51.060
Once someone gets the whole story

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:52.270
and they understand why they

00:03:52.270 --> 00:03:53.720
should be buying your product or service,

00:03:53.720 --> 00:03:55.540
and then you have a call to action.

00:03:55.540 --> 00:03:57.230
They're much more likely to convert.

00:03:57.230 --> 00:03:59.347
What most people like doing is saying,

00:03:59.347 --> 00:04:00.610
"Hey, here's what I'm selling."

00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:02.680
And above the fold, they
just put a call to action,

00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:04.420
like click this, here's some more details,

00:04:04.420 --> 00:04:06.140
click this, here's some more details,

00:04:06.140 --> 00:04:06.973
click this.

00:04:06.973 --> 00:04:08.310
And what you'll find is

00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:10.190
someone doesn't get the full picture,

00:04:10.190 --> 00:04:11.780
so then when they go to the checkout page,

00:04:11.780 --> 00:04:13.030
or the lead form page,

00:04:13.030 --> 00:04:15.420
the conversion from visitor
to filling out the lead.

00:04:15.420 --> 00:04:17.290
or visitor to checking out,

00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:18.300
is much lower.

00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:19.940
It's not about getting
the most amount of people

00:04:19.940 --> 00:04:21.660
to your checkout or lead form pages.

00:04:21.660 --> 00:04:24.300
It's about getting the
highest number of completions.

00:04:24.300 --> 00:04:26.460
So yeah, you may not get as many clicks,

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:29.730
but if everyone who visits
those pages converts,

00:04:29.730 --> 00:04:31.210
you could be better off.

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:32.960
And that's why you want to answer

00:04:32.960 --> 00:04:34.880
all the objections, the benefits,

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:37.950
have your main heading,
have your main visual focus,

00:04:37.950 --> 00:04:40.020
and then go into your call to action.

00:04:40.020 --> 00:04:42.027
Versus just being like "Hey,

00:04:42.027 --> 00:04:43.107
"land on my landing page,

00:04:43.107 --> 00:04:45.340
"you came here, click
this and buy right away."

00:04:45.340 --> 00:04:46.417
because most people are going to be like,

00:04:46.417 --> 00:04:48.450
"Sorry, see you later."

00:04:48.450 --> 00:04:49.760
The fifth thing you want to do

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:52.580
is include testimonials
and other visual proof.

00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:53.910
I love doing reviews,

00:04:53.910 --> 00:04:56.020
whether it's a service or a product.

00:04:56.020 --> 00:04:57.120
Reviews are amazing.

00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:58.700
A reason a reviews is amazing

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:00.530
is people know the truth.

00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:01.890
How they feel, how they don't feel,

00:05:01.890 --> 00:05:03.370
if it's great or if it's bad.

00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:05.780
And by including that, they can then

00:05:05.780 --> 00:05:07.680
get a better sense if it's right for them,

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:10.030
or if it's not a good fit for them.

00:05:10.030 --> 00:05:12.610
The sixth thing you need
to do is give a guarantee.

00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:14.600
Whether you're doing a free
trial with no credit card,

00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:15.560
so there's low risk,

00:05:15.560 --> 00:05:18.740
or you're giving a 30 day or 60 day

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:19.890
money-back guarantee,

00:05:19.890 --> 00:05:20.900
those are awesome things.

00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:22.540
You want people to feel comfortable.

00:05:22.540 --> 00:05:24.030
If they're not happy, you know

00:05:24.030 --> 00:05:25.830
you're going to end up
refunding them anyways.

00:05:25.830 --> 00:05:27.100
If you don't, in the long run,

00:05:27.100 --> 00:05:28.730
it's going to tarnish your brand.

00:05:28.730 --> 00:05:30.160
Look, we're not all perfect.

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:32.010
We all get complaints, even I do.

00:05:32.010 --> 00:05:33.770
And when we do, what do you try to do?

00:05:33.770 --> 00:05:34.830
You solve them.

00:05:34.830 --> 00:05:36.780
That's why the guarantee's important.

00:05:36.780 --> 00:05:39.570
Because the moment you can
solve these problems for people,

00:05:39.570 --> 00:05:41.310
and show that you're there and you care,

00:05:41.310 --> 00:05:43.670
they're more likely to convert.

00:05:43.670 --> 00:05:46.210
The last step, integrate story telling

00:05:46.210 --> 00:05:47.820
into your landing page.

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:49.980
If you don't integrate story telling,

00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:52.230
you'll find that your
conversions won't do as well.

00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:53.930
People love soap operas.

00:05:53.930 --> 00:05:56.240
Whether you like them
personally or not, people do.

00:05:56.240 --> 00:05:58.960
That's why they're on television 24-seven.

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:01.170
If you can integrate story telling,

00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:03.120
take people through the
emotional roller coasters,

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:06.640
the ups, the downs, they're
much more likely to convert.

00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:08.150
It's all about the story.

00:06:08.150 --> 00:06:11.040
It's that thousand-plus
year old marketing technique

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:12.770
that we all tend to forget.

00:06:12.770 --> 00:06:14.090
But it's worked for so many years,

00:06:14.090 --> 00:06:15.430
and it'll still keep working,

00:06:15.430 --> 00:06:17.090
no matter what channels are out there,

00:06:17.090 --> 00:06:19.090
no matter what algorithm updates happen.

00:06:19.090 --> 00:06:20.670
Story telling is so effective,

00:06:20.670 --> 00:06:23.070
you need to use it in all
of your landing pages.

00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:23.960
Thank you for watching.

00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:26.670
And if you need help with
your conversion optimization,

00:06:26.670 --> 00:06:29.520
check out my ad agency,
Neil Patel Digital.

00:06:29.520 --> 00:06:30.720
Make sure you leave a comment,

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:33.000
subscribe, tell the
people about this video.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:33.833
Cheers.

